CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 17, 1946, pg. 17 reads: "Horseplay - Russell B. Muldrew practices first aid on Coach William Seay as Officer Stanford Brown gives a hand. It's all in fun!  This act was one of the hilarious skits presented by the Centre Avenue YMCA in the mammoth water circus at Ammon Pool last Friday.  The event was a feature of Frog Week activities. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Russell B. Muldrew practices first aid on Coach William Seay as Stanford Brown helps on right during a skit performed at Ammon Pool for Water Circus during Frogs Week
